main event: A missile engineer reported seeing an unidentified flying object near Holloman Air Force Base.
interesting points: The sighting lasted for 6 minutes and involved 5 witnesses,The object hovered about 10 degrees above the horizon before disappearing,The object was described as cigar-shaped with a fan-shaped tail and lights resembling portholes,Further investigation concluded that the sighting was misidentified as an F-106 aircraft,There were no official reports of flying objects during that time from the Air Force installations.
sighted object: cigar-shaped object with a fan-shaped tail and lights
witness description: missile engineer and four other persons
